#Text=Monday , January 23 , 2012 .
#Text=If you believe any of these stories deserves more in-depth coverage , feel free to write a full article on the issues raised .
#Text=Western show of unity in the Strait of Hormuz on the eve of further anti-Iran sanctions
#Text=A six-strong flotilla of United States , French , and British warships , centered around the USS Abraham Lincoln , has sailed through the Strait of Hormuz .
#Text=The move comes on the eve of an expected embargo on the import of Iranian oil by the European Union , and an Iranian threat to close the straits to international shipping .
#Text=Thirty five percent of the world 's supply of crude oil passes through the Strait of Hormuz .
#Text=David Blair .
#Text=" Britain , US and France send warships through Strait of Hormuz " — The Telegraph , January 23 , 2012
#Text=Don Mackay .
#Text=" Britain sends warship to join international flotilla after threats by Iran over oil embargo " — Daily Mirror , January 22 , 2012

column1: #Text=Libyan deputy leader resigns over protests
#Text=Abdul Hafiz Ghoga , the vice-chair of Libya 's National Transitional Council ( NTC ) resigned following protests in Benghazi on Saturday .
#Text=Talking to Al Jazeera on Sunday he said , " [ m]y resignation is for the benefit of the nation and is required at this stage .

column1: #Text=" Libya ’s NTC Deputy Head Quits After Benghazi Protests " — Voice of America , January 22 , 2012
#Text=Nigeria death toll set to rise

#Text=The confirmed death toll of 178 in co-ordinated attacks against Nigerian government targets in Kano on Friday , with police and soldiers amongst the many dead and wounded , is expected to rise .

#Text=Attacks by Boko Haram , who seek to create an Islamic state , are becoming increasingly sophisticated , with fears the group aims to provoke a civil war between Nigeria 's Muslim north and Christian south .
#Text=Reuters .
#Text=" Nigerian police say four Boko Haram members killed " — Reuters ( UK ) , January 23 , 2012
#Text=" Nigerian President Visits Kano , Site of Deadly Attacks " — Voice of America , January 22 , 2012
#Text=Economy not Sharia will be the focus of Egypt 's new Islamic government
#Text=Improving the economy and fighting poverty , not legislating to create a Muslim state , will be the Muslim Brotherhood 's agenda when they form Egypt 's first post- Mubarak government today .

#Text=" We ca n't talk about implementing Islamic Shariah law when the country is experiencing such devastating economic problems , " said Mohammed Gouda , a party policymaker and economics committee member .
#Text=Islamists form a majority in the new assembly with the Muslim Brotherhood winning 46 % of seats and the conservative Al-Nour Party 23 % .
#Text=Hadeel al-Shalchi .
#Text=" Egypt Islamists on eve of power ease talk of Islam " — Associated Press , January 22 , 2012
#Text=Heba Saleh .
#Text=" New parliament marks radical shift in Egyptian politics " — Financial Times , January 22 , 2012
#Text=UK unemployment increases to 2.68m as profit warnings increase
#Text=The UK 's unemployment rate has reached 8.4 % — 2.685 million people — according to data released by the Office of National Statistics .
#Text=The figure reflects the quarter ending last November and is a 0.3 % increase on the previous quarter .

#Text=Unemployment amongst younger people now stands at 22.3 % — 1.043 million people , and the number of people claiming Jobseekers ' Allowance has now reached 1.6 million ; in December , 1,200 new claimants began receiving unemployment benefits .
#Text=Profit warnings from firms within the UK have increased from 51 in the third quarter to 88 in the fourth , say Ernst & Young .
#Text=The nation saw 206 firms issue 278 warnings profits were not as high as initially expected .

#Text=Three years after British retailer Woolworths collapsed , 24,000 who lost their jobs as a result have won a fight for compensation ; each will receive 60 days ' pay , a total payout of £ 67.8 million and averaging £2,800 per person .
#Text=Katie Linsell .
#Text=" U.K. Quarterly Profit Warnings Rise 70 % , Ernst & Young Says " — Bloomberg , January 22 , 2012
#Text=" Profit warnings in UK ' up 70 % in fourth quarter ' " — BBC News Online , January 22 , 2012
#Text=Rory Reynolds .
#Text=" Former Woolworths staff to be paid millions in compensation after employment tribunal victory " — Scotland on Sunday , January 22 , 2012
